data.name: Libra Speciality Chemicals
data.description: For over 50 years Libra has been setting the standards in the provision of high-quality products and services to the chemical industry. Our formula for success has been and will continue to be total customer satisfaction; it is the driving force behind everything we do. Our award-winning service has touched all corners of the globe, managing relations and communications of all sizes and providing a total chemical manufacturing service no matter the requirements of your company.

data.name: Librateric
data.description: Librateric at both high and low active concentrations manufactured with either HCNO, PKO or fatty acid and either sodium benzoate or high pH used a preservation. It is fully REACH registered for sale worldwide and delivers excellent value along with market leading manufacturing and sustainability standards.

data.name: Libranol
data.description: Libranol series of alkonolamides are a range of non-ionic surfactants that are highly compatible with most surfactant types. The compound is a viscous liquid which produces moderate foam, as well as possessing wetting and thickening properties. Alkanolamines commonly possess applications for the personal care industry, in products such as shampoo and other soaps; as well as a variety of cleaning products in the household, industrial, and institutional cleaning sectors.

data.name: Libranox
data.description: Libranox series of amine oxides are excellent detergents and cleaners for global cleaning industries and sectors. The series can be applied to cleaning products, they perform as excellent detergents, as well as providing excellent foam boosting and foam stabilising properties. When used in combination with anionics like sodium lauryl ether sulphate (SLES), the detergency effect of the formulation is increased. The products are also extensively used with both sodium hypochlorite and hydrogen peroxide to produce bleach based products. The dense, stable foam produced can be used in the formulation of high alkalinity cleaning compounds.

data.name: Libradet
data.description: Libradet: formulated products are a synergistic blend of surfactants and foam stabilisers. Its ability to create a high-foaming product with consistent bubble size means it is well-suited to the production of lightweight foamed concrete.

data.name: Libramul
data.description: Libramul IPA is a clear yellow-to-amber liquid product that contains isopropylamine dodecylbenzene sulphonate. As an anionic surfactant, it exhibits compatibility with both other anionic and nonionic surfactants. This versatile amine salt serves as an effective emulsifying agent for various substances, including organic solvents, waxes, and mineral oils. It is particularly well-suited for producing emulsion degreasers and kerosene-based hand-cleaning gels.

data.name: Libraphos
data.description: Libraphos series of phosphate esters from Libra Speciality Chemicals are anionic surfactants, suitable for use in a wide range of applicants and industries. The Libraphos series are 100% active anionic surfactants and are based on alcohols, aromatic ethoxylates or alcohol ethoxylates. Libraphos phosphate esters are manufactured by either a polyphosphoric acid route giving predominantly mono esters or by a phosphorous pentoxide route to give predominantly di-esters. These phosphate esters can then be neutralised to achieve a variety of salts. The Libraphos series of surfactants may be used in a number of applications due to their stability at high temperatures or in acidic or alkaline conditions. These attributes offer significant advantages over other surfactants.

data.name: Libranone
data.description: The Libranone series contains a range of nonionic surfactant dilutions together with a number of formulated products for use in a wide range of industrial applications.Â Our range of Alcohol Ethoxylates can be ingredients in a range of formulations in global industries. The range is an environmentally friendly and acceptable alternative with strong performance features that improve on previous products like Alkyl Phenol Ethoxylates that have been phased out of the surfactant market.

data.name: Libratex
data.description: Libratex series of anionic surfactants consists of dodecylbenzene sulphonic acid, its neutralised salts and dioctyl sulphosuccinates. These products are compatible with other anionic and nonionic surfactants and may be used as raw materials in the manufacture of a wide range of detergent products. The Libratex Series of products are soluble in a number of liquids from aqueous to organic solvents.

data.name: LibraCare APG 0810-60
data.description: LibraCare APG 0810-60 is a nonionic surfactant, offering exceptional biodegradability and deriving from renewable resources. With low toxicity, this product is in liquid formulation and serves in oil and gas applications, providing effective surfactant properties. LibraCare APG 0810-60 maintains environmentally conscious attributes.

data.name: Libranox AO14-30
data.description: Libranox AO14-30 functions as a detergent and is available in liquid form. It boasts features such as foam stability, degreasing, foam enhancement, effective soil removal, high foaming, emulsifying properties, excellent cleaning performance, good compatibility, detergency, improved foam stability, and increased viscosity. This product holds certifications for RSPO Certified Sustainable Palm Oil, ISO 14001, ISO 45001, and ISO 9001. It is used in various applications, including alkaline cleaners, detergents, and industrial cleaners.

data.name: Libranone G/100/080 90
data.description: Libranone G/100/080 90 is a non-ionic surfactant containing 2-propyl-heptanol with 8 moles of EO. This formulation is a slightly cloudy pasty liquid and is well-regarded for its exceptional compatibility with soaps, anionic, cationic, and other non-ionic surfactants. Libranone G/100/080 90 is commonly used as a wetting agent in various applications.

data.name: Librateric BA70

summary.name: Chemical Name
items: 2-Propenoic acid, methyl ester, reaction products with 2-ethyl-1-hexanamine and sodium hydroxide

data.description: Librateric BA70 is a liquid formulation featuring 2-ethylhexyl imino dipropionate, potassium salt. This versatile product finds applications in various industries, including detergents, foaming agents, emulsifiers, hydrotropes, low foamers, and antifoams. It is also beneficial in the oil and gas sector, where it serves as a dispersant, emulsifier, foamer, wetting agent, anti-corrosive, and lubricant aid, demonstrating its adaptability and utility in various formulations.

data.name: Libranone C40 96%
data.description: Libranone C40 96% is a non-ionic surfactant composed of castor oil with 40 moles EO. This formulation is a clear amber liquid with dispersible solubility in water. Libranone C40 96% is highly regarded for its outstanding compatibility with soaps, anionic, cationic, and other non-ionic surfactants.

data.name: Libranone 91/080
data.description: Libranone 91/080 is a nonionic surfactant containing oxo alcohol C9 - C11 with 8 moles EO. This formulation is clear to cloudy pale yellow liquid and is highly recognized for its outstanding compatibility with soaps, anionic, cationic, and other nonionic surfactants. Libranone 91/080 serves as a surfactant and wetting agent in a variety of applications, including industrial cleaners, textiles, domestic washing up liquids, and vehicle cleaning.

data.name: Libraphos 1028

summary.name: Chemical Name
items: Phosphoric Acid Ester of Ethoxylated (POE8) Isotridecyl Alcohol

data.description: Libraphos 1028 is a clear to slightly hazy, pale-yellow liquid containing isotridecyl alcohol ethoxylate phosphate ester. This product exhibits anionic characteristics, making it compatible with both other anionic and nonionic surfactants. Libraphos 1028 is highly stable in acidic and alkaline systems, even at elevated temperatures. It finds various applications, such as enhancing wetting, emulsification, providing lubricity, detergency, and corrosion inhibition.

data.name: Libranone C40
data.description: Libranone C40 is a liquid industrial additive falling under the oil, gas, and mining chemicals category. Known for its low foaming feature, Libranone C40 functions as a nonionic surfactant. The product also boasts environmentally friendly attributes, supporting sustainable industrial practices.

data.name: Librateric CAB30 HA
data.description: Librateric CAB30 HA is a self-preserving betaine with high pH (high alkalinity) and is derived from hydrogenated (hardened) coconut oil. This product, based on hydrogenated coconut oil, is designed to minimize color and odor. It offers excellent viscosity enhancement and foam-boosting properties for anionic-based cleansers.

data.name: Libratex DOS70E
data.description: Libratex DOS70E is a solution containing 70% Sodium di-octyl sulphosuccinate in water or ethanol. This product exhibits dispersible solubility in water and is highly versatile in various applications. As an anionic substance, Libratex DOS70E is compatible with both anionic and nonionic surfactants. It serves as an effective dispersant in the formulation of coatings, inks, and latex emulsions. Furthermore, it plays a vital role in emulsifying oils and solvents, particularly in conjunction with nonionic surfactants, offering enhanced stability at high temperatures.

data.name: Libratex DOS70K
data.description: Libratex DOS70K is a solution containing 70% di-octylsulphosuccinate in odorless kerosene. This product is insoluble in water but has a wide range of applications in oil and solvent systems. As an anionic substance, Libratex DOS70K is compatible with both anionic and nonionic surfactants. It is particularly valuable in agricultural formulations, where it aids in the emulsification of oils and solvents. Additionally, it finds use in lubricants, dispersants, and paints, offering excellent wetting abilities and oil solubility, enhancing performance in these applications.

data.name: Libratex AS 10
data.description: Libratex AS 10 is a clear straw-to-pale yellow liquid formulation featuring ammonium dodecylbenzene sulphonate in water. This versatile product plays a key role as a primary emulsifier in emulsion polymerization processes, contributing to the creation of a wide range of products. Its applications span various industries where emulsion polymerization is a fundamental process for manufacturing a multitude of goods.

data.name: Libratex DOS60PG
data.description: Libratex DOS 60PG is a clear/slightly hazy, viscous pale-yellow liquid formulation containing 60% di-octylsulphosuccinate in water or MPG. This anionic product is known for its compatibility with other anionic and nonionic surfactants. Libratex DOS 60PG is commonly used in oil and solvent emulsification, often in conjunction with non-ionic surfactants, to achieve enhanced high-temperature stability, making it an ideal choice for various applications.

data.name: Libratex DOS60E
data.description: Libratex DOS60E is a clear/slightly hazy pale yellow liquid formulation featuring 60% di-octyl sulphosuccinate in water/ethanol. This versatile product is widely recognized for its role in oil and solvent emulsification, especially when combined with nonionic surfactants, resulting in improved high-temperature stability. Additionally, Libratex DOS60E is utilized as a dispersant in various applications, including coatings, inks, and latex emulsions, contributing to the creation of stable and effective formulations.

data.name: Libratex DOS 70PG
data.description: Libratex DOS70PG is a clear/slightly hazy liquid formulation containing 70% Sodium di-octyl sulphosuccinate in water or MPG. This anionic product is known for its compatibility with other anionic and nonionic surfactants. Libratex DOS70PG serves various purposes in aqueous systems, particularly as a dispersant for coatings, inks, and latex emulsions. Additionally, it can be combined with nonionic surfactants to enhance high-temperature stability, making it a valuable addition to diverse applications.

data.name: Libratex MS3
data.description: Libratex MS3 (MB) is preserved with 0.9% phenoxyethanol. This naturally based and light-colored product finds utility in various personal care applications. It is particularly effective in generating dense foam when combined with SLES, making it an ideal component for use in shampoo, foam baths, and body wash formulations.

data.name: Libratex NSA
data.description: Libratex NSA is a slightly viscous brown liquid formulation composed of dodecylbenzene sulphonic acid (Narrow cut). This versatile product, along with its various neutralized forms, plays a crucial role as a foaming agent, wetting agent, and emulsifier. It finds widespread use in detergents and emulsion polymerization processes, contributing to the production of various products across industries.

data.name: Libratex SLES 2-28

data.description: Libratex SLES 2-28 is a 27% active solution of sodium lauryl (2 moles) ether sulfate, derived from natural alcohol and preserved with a high pH. This pale yellow liquid serves as a surfactant in a wide range of applications, including cosmetics, household, and industrial cleaning, as well as foaming applications.

This sulfate is derived from natural alcohol and is preserved with a high pH. It serves as a surfactant in various applications, including cosmetics, household, industrial cleaning, and foaming applications.

data.name: Libratex DOS60K
data.description: Libratex DOS60K is an anionic surfactant classified under the chemical family of sulfosuccinates and sulfosuccinamates. In its liquid form, this industrial additive is specifically designed for oil and gas applications, proving to be a versatile solution. Libratex DOS60K finds application in emulsion polymerization processes, showcasing its adaptability across various industrial manufacturing methods.
